&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview:&lt;/strong&gt; RCLCO is a leading real estate consulting firm specializing in providing strategic advisory services to clients in the real estate industry. With a rich history and an esteemed reputation, RCLCO is dedicated to shaping the future of real estate through insightful analysis, innovative strategies, and unparalleled client service. RCLCO has offices in Austin, Denver, Los Angeles, New York, Orlando, San Francisco, and Washington, DC, and offers an array of consulting services across three major service areas: Real Estate Economics; Management Consulting (including Talent Advisory); and RCLCO Fund Advisors, an affiliate firm focused on institutional real estate investment strategy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary: &lt;/strong&gt;RCLCO seeks a qualified Vice President for our Compensation Consulting team, with a strong preference for someone based in Washington, DC. This role will lead and execute on consulting engagements alongside the Managing Director and serve as a trusted advisor to C-suite leadership, Board of Directors, and Human Resources on all matters related to compensation strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate for this position has demonstrated knowledge of the commercial real estate industry, including typical functions and roles, capitalization, asset classes, and GP/LP structures. The individual has strong judgement and problem-solving skills, operates with a sense of urgency, is comfortable working in an entrepreneurial, high growth environment, is a savvy communicator and presenter, and can advance project work autonomously. The role will include a range of tasks, and may look different day-to-day, though can be highlighted generally as shown below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Job Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the engagement leader for compensation consulting projects, handling all client communications and ensuring deadlines are met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in business development efforts including joining introductory calls with new clients and developing engagement letters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop short- and long-term incentive plan recommendations that reflect market norms and client needs, preferences, and philosophy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct research via external sources and RCLCO’s internal databases to identify appropriate market comparisons for compensation benchmarking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate, through both written memoranda and presentations, key findings and recommendations to clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review work produced by junior team members and provide regular feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a thought partner for ongoing enhancements to RCLCO’s annual Real Estate Compensation &amp;amp; Benefits Survey, which is the industry’s most comprehensive compensation survey, representing over 400 companies nationwide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead efforts to drive continuous improvements and enhance teamwide processes, templates, and databases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Years of professional experience: 7+ years, ideally in commercial real estate, private equity, or financial services&lt;/li&gt;
